{"key":"processedPost-9862295","value":{"id":9862295,"first":9862034,"last":9952877,"when":1235588860,"utime":"02/25/09 09:07 PM","content":"Use gypsum, but don't use the lime, since you don't need or want to pH adjust coir.&nbsp; Add coffee grinds if you have them, or a small amount of composted chicken manure will also add a lot of bang.&nbsp; Use no more than 5% chicken manure if you go that route(1/2 part to 10).<br /><br />Never pressure cook bulk substrates.&nbsp; It makes them far more likely to contaminate.&nbsp; Simply hydrate the coir to field capacity and pasteurize at 60C to 70C for one hour, measured at the center of the substrate being heat treated.<br /><br />Make sure your popcorn spawn isn't contaminated.&nbsp; It's extremely prone to bacteria contamination, especially when inoculated with untested LC.<br />RR<br />RR","title":"Re: Spawning to coir-question"}}